# Branding & Visual Identity
- Always use the color palette defined in `tailwind.config.js` (primary, secondary, accent).
- Base all UI designs on the "spirit" of the community logo (logo.jpg). 
- If the logo is traditional, lean towards Serif fonts and classic spacing. If modern, use Sans-serif and clean, minimalist layouts.
- Buttons: Primary actions must use the `accent` color. Secondary actions use `secondary` or outlined styles.

# RTL & Hebrew Support
- This is a Hebrew-first application. All layouts must be Right-to-Left (RTL).
- Use `rtl` utility classes where necessary and ensure that icons (like arrows) are flipped correctly for RTL.
- All user-facing strings must be in Hebrew unless specified otherwise.

# Component Consistency
- Every new page or component must include the community logo in the header or a consistent branding element.
- Maintain a "clean and family-friendly" aesthetic: generous whitespace, clear typography, and no aggressive or dark-themed UI by default.